—————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
Script List (Main Purpose)
—————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————

chr_mafft.py                           (Monomer/Subunit Fine Mapping)
1-samples_satellite.py                 (Subunit → Monomer → HOR → Visualization)
2-samples_satellite.py                 (Homogenization Analysis)
3-stat_plot.py                         (Summary & Statistics)

chr2blast.py                           (Satellite Fast Finding)
chr2moddotplot3.py                     (Repeat Detection by ModDotPlot)

chr2aligntime.py                       (Divergence Time: Database-dependent)
chr2aligntime_DIY.py                   (Divergence Time: Standalone)
chr2aligntime_collinearity.py          (Collinearity Plot)

chr2EDTA.py                            (TE Annotation & Phylogeny)
chr2TEsorter.py                        (TE Visualization)
chr2soloLTRs.py                        (Solo LTR Analysis)

chr2LIRinfo.py                         (LIR Satellite Analysis)



—————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
Script Introduction
—————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
chr_mafft.py
This script performs precise identification and characterization of satellite repeat monomers using MAFFT-based alignment against a reference monomer template. It is specifically designed for short monomers (<50 bp) where traditional BLAST-based methods lack precision.

1-samples_satellite.py
This script provides comprehensive population-level analysis of satellite repeats across multiple grapevine genomes, integrating monomer identification, UMAP dimensionality reduction, HOR (Higher-Order Repeat) detection, and statistical visualization.

2-samples_satellite.py
This module analyzes sequence homogenization within centromeric satellite arrays by calculating k-mer-based entropy metrics across sliding windows.

3-stat_plot.py
This script mainly summarizes satellite repeat data generated by the chr2blast and samples_satellite pipelines.

chr2blast.py
This script performs rapid genome-wide localization of satellite repeats using BLAST. It is designed for initial, coarse-grained identification of tandem repeat arrays, particularly suited for monomers >50 bp. For precise boundary definition of shorter monomers (<50 bp), the companion script chr_mafft.py is recommended.

chr2moddotplot3.py
Extension of ModDotPlot usage: Batch identification of large segmental duplications and large inverted repeats based on BED files. The results require auxiliary filtering based on genomic location and repeat structure type, and even manual verification.

chr2aligntime.py
Calculates divergence time between two genomic regions based on k-mer matching and MAFFT alignment. Designed for flexible pairwise comparison of any two regions from the genome database.

chr2aligntime_DIY.py
Calculates divergence time between two sequences from a single FASTA file. This is the standalone, database-independent version of chr2aligntime.py.

chr2aligntime_collinearity.py
Batch processing wrapper for chr2aligntime.py. Performs pairwise comparisons on consecutive regions and generates a combined collinearity plot.

chr2EDTA.py
This script provides a comprehensive pipeline for TE annotation, classification, phylogenetic analysis, and integration with centromere satellite data in grapevine genomes.

chr2TEsorter.py
This script performs targeted TE annotation and visualization for user-defined genomic regions. It integrates TEsorter for TE classification, ModDotPlot for self-alignment visualization, and BLAST for satellite repeat detection.

chr2soloLTRs.py
This script performs genome-wide identification, classification, and phylogenetic analysis of solo LTR retrotransposons, with a focus on Tekay/ClassII elements in grapevine genomes.

chr2LIRinfo.py
This script analyzes the distribution, classification, and evolutionary timing of LIR satellites (LIRSat1/2/3) in grapevine genomes, integrating TE annotation and divergence time estimation.




